##################################################################
##################################################################
This project attempts to implement a compiler from
ATS3 to CC (that is, C/C++).
##################################################################
HX-2026-02-22: Compiling to C!
I have just started the phase of compiling ATS3 to C.
Compared to compiling to JS, compiling to C additionally requires
handling of types (for data) and closure formation (for functions).
##################################################################
HX-2026-03-11:
#
I went ahead to use XSYNCPY for implementing XATS2CC. Soon I
realized that XSYNCPY does not yet handle template resolution,
causing me to abandon the implementation. As of now, I plan
to implement XATS2CC based on the systax tree obtained immediately
after trtmp3a and trtmp3b.
#
One significant issue that needs to be dealt with is the handling
of constructor projection (D3Epcon).
##################################################################
HX-2026-03-28:
See ATS3-Xanadu/srcgen2/xats2cc for the work on closure formation.
